This paper describes a planner that combines temporal and numeric reasoning, making advances in the expressive reasoning capabilities of planners. The paper is likely to be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with planning and heuristic search. It may also be categorized under Programming Languages (cs.PL) as it discusses the use of PDDL2.1. The paper also mentions the use of Linear Programming (LP) and mixed integer programming, which are topics in Linear Algebra (cs.LG) and Robotics (cs.RO) respectively. Finally, the paper's focus on planning and optimization in the context of continuous change suggests it may also be categorized under Systems and Control (cs.SY).
